This paper focuses on the use of generative models for image generation and the unsupervised discovery and control of semantic attributes. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category, as it deals with image analysis and generation. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of mutual information maximization and total correlation minimization, which are techniques commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.LG, cs.AI). The paper also mentions the disentanglement of latent factors, which is a topic often studied in neural networks and computational neuroscience (cs.NE). Finally, the paper reports experiments on image datasets, which suggests that it may also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
